<div1 type="trialAccount" id="t17610225-32">
               <interp inst="t17610225-32" type="collection" value="BAILEY"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17610225-32" type="year" value="1761"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17610225-32" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/17610225"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17610225-32" type="date" value="17610225"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17610225-32-off156-c287" targOrder="Y" targets="t17610225-32-defend344 t17610225-32-off156 t17610225-32-verdict160"></join>
         
               <p>111. (L.) 
               <persName id="t17610225-32-defend344" type="defendantName">
                  Isaac 
                  Hall , otherwise <rs id="t17610225-32-alias-3" type="alias">
                        <join result="nameAlias" targOrder="Y" targets="t17610225-32-defend344 t17610225-32-alias-3"></join>Howse</rs>
                     <interp inst="t17610225-32-defend344" type="surname" value="Hall"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17610225-32-defend344" type="given" value="Isaac"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17610225-32-defend344" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , was indicted for <rs id="t17610225-32-off156" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17610225-32-off156" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17610225-32-off156" type="offenceSubcategory" value="grandLarceny"></interp>
               stealing one cambrick handkerchief, value 2 s. 6 d.
            </rs> the property of 
               
                  <persName id="t17610225-32-victim346" type="victimName">
                     Thomas 
                     Hurnall 
                  <interp inst="t17610225-32-victim346" type="surname" value="Hurnall"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17610225-32-victim346" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17610225-32-victim346" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17610225-32-off156 t17610225-32-victim346"></join>
                  </persName>
                
            , <rs id="t17610225-32-viclabel157" type="occupation">Esq</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17610225-32-victim346 t17610225-32-viclabel157"></join>; <rs id="t17610225-32-cd158" type="crimeDate">Feb. 9</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17610225-32-off156 t17610225-32-cd158"></join>.~</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17610225-32-person347">
                  Thomas 
                  Hurnall 
               <interp inst="t17610225-32-person347" type="surname" value="Hurnall"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17610225-32-person347" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17610225-32-person347" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . Coming down <placeName id="t17610225-32-crimeloc159">Fleet-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17610225-32-crimeloc159" type="placeName" value="Fleet-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17610225-32-crimeloc159" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17610225-32-off156 t17610225-32-crimeloc159"></join> on the 9th of February, between eight and nine o'clock in the evening, I felt something at my pocket, I turned about, the prisoner was closest<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="176102250058"></xptr> of all to me on my right hand; I took him by the collar, and said, you dog, you have picked my pocket of my handkerchief. I felt and found it was gone. I said I would take him into a shop just by. Another man came up and said, what are you doing with that man? he is as honest a man as any in England; then said I I'll have you in; he soon disappeared: I took the prisoner in, then the man in the shop, 
               <persName id="t17610225-32-person348">
                  William 
                  Hore 
               <interp inst="t17610225-32-person348" type="surname" value="Hore"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17610225-32-person348" type="given" value="William"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17610225-32-person348" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , said, he saw the prisoner take my handkerchief out of my pocket. I saw it lying on the ground, it was taken up and given to me; the prisoner was dressed then like a gentleman, not as he is now; he said he was just come from sea.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17610225-32-person349">
                  William 
                  Hore 
               <interp inst="t17610225-32-person349" type="surname" value="Hore"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17610225-32-person349" type="given" value="William"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17610225-32-person349" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was shutting up our shop in Fleet-street, I saw the prisoner take a white handkerchief out of the prosecutor's pocket, and I called to the prosecutor; then the prisoner drop'd it close to a post, I took it up, and delivered it either to the prosecutor or a person talking to him. [Produced and deposed to.] There was no body so near the prosecutor as the prisoner was, and I was about two yards from them.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17610225-32-person350">
                  Thomas 
                  Peirshaw 
               <interp inst="t17610225-32-person350" type="surname" value="Peirshaw"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17610225-32-person350" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17610225-32-person350" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the constable that took the prisoner to Bridewell; he refused going along, and was within a little of making his escape from me.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence.</p>
               <p>There were several people as near the prosecutor as I was; he searched me, and found nothing upon me. I was just come home from sea.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17610225-32-verdict160" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17610225-32-verdict160" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               Guilty
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17610225-32-punish161" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17610225-32-punish161" type="punishmentCategory" value="transport"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t17610225-32-defend344 t17610225-32-punish161"></join>
               
                     <note>[Transportation. See summary.]</note>
               
                  </rs>
               </p>
            </div1>
